  <entry>
    <id>tag:github.com,2008:Grit::Commit/15d1056b537a07b613f6dfe56fc920390c1dd267</id>
    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/commit/15d1056b537a07b613f6dfe56fc920390c1dd267"/>
    <title>
        Implement equally sized bars (#4994)
    </title>
    <updated>2017-12-02T11:38:36Z</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/3874900?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>simonbrunel</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/simonbrunel</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;pre style=&#39;white-space:pre-wrap;width:81ex&#39;&gt;Implement equally sized bars (#4994)

When `barThickness: undefined|null` (default), we compute an optimal sample size based on the smallest tick interval reduced to prevent any bar to overlap (bar equally sized). Also added support for a special `barThickness: &amp;#39;flex&amp;#39;` value (previous default) that globally arranges bars side by side to prevent any gap when percentage options are 1 (variable bar sizes).&lt;/pre&gt;
    </content>
  </entry>
